6180k double-fee estimate uses this number; if the real base is 60\'96100 trackable placements, the numbers move. "Sara is a volume-at-mix problem, not a conversion problem." Sharp framing, but her 87% conversion may be high precisely because she qualifies tightly and rejects briefs she can't fill. Pushing more briefs through her pipeline may not preserve 87%. The blueprint asserts this without evidence. The "cap BD calls at 60\'9670% during interim ramp" recommendation. Directly contradicts Sara's own business plan with a confidence the blueprint doesn't earn. It's a strong claim that needs more than assertion. Universe-wide scan caricature. The blueprint repeatedly characterises our final stack as "universe-wide daily scan as centrepiece, 1,250-profile openness radar, predictive talent-flow model dominate the current draft." By the end of our iteration we had cut the openness radar, never had the talent-flow model in the final stack, and our universe-wide scan had watchlist weighting. The blueprint is partly arguing against the original ceiling-doc PDF, not what we landed on. Where our work was probably right and the blueprint dismisses it without enough evidence Our four on-demand commands match the blueprint's Skills 3, 4, 5 and /shortlist exactly. No disagreement. Our placed-candidate watch with both leaver's-next-employer and old-employer succession matches the blueprint's Skill 1 structure. Our compliance posture is directionally correct; less detailed but the same shape. Net assessment, honest The blueprint identifies real gaps in our work \'97 interim desk, roundtable engine, cross-sell map, IC platform inversion, Sales Nav ToS, Cloud Routines caps, model routing, DUAA specifics. These are genuine and material.\
The blueprint also over-claims its yield numbers, treats unsourced estimates as empirical findings, partly argues against a strawman version of our final stack, and packages aspirational additive math as "evidence-based ceiling." The \'a3620\'96780k number is not the result of careful arithmetic \'97 it's the result of summing optimistic line items and rounding down by an unstated amount.\
The honest position: the blueprint's architectural recommendations are mostly better than ours (interim Skill, roundtable Skill, cross-sell map, narrow Tier-1 + weekly batch, model routing). The blueprint's yield projections are not credible at the level of confidence presented and would need tempering before being repeated as forecasts.\
What this means practically: take the blueprint's six-Skill structure and platform corrections seriously. Discount the \'a3620\'96780k headline to roughly \'a3500\'96650k as a more defensible band, with most of that uplift over your \'a3338k base coming from interim (realistic year-1 \'a3200\'96280k), retained conversions (\'a360\'96100k), roundtables (\'a3100\'96200k if disciplined), and past-placement double-fee (\'a350\'96120k). Less than the blueprint claims. Still materially more than what our final stack would deliver.\
