On the recalibrated numbers (\'a3500-700k). They're more defensible than \'a3620-780k but still estimates, not arithmetic. Any specific yield range from this exercise is speculation. The honest position is "we don't know the yield; the architecture doesn't depend on knowing it."\
Does it change the tool we build? Mostly no. Three small adjustments.\
The architecture is reactive to Sara's existing operational reality, not to yield projections:\
The interim Skill exists because she has 24 interims as a stated target, not because the model predicts \'a3360k or \'a3270k from it The roundtable Skill exists because she has four roundtables in her plan, not because we predict any specific conversion rate The placed-candidate sensor exists because the mechanic is real, not because we forecast \'a390-180k or \'a360-140k The compliance stack is mandatory regardless of yield The platform corrections (Cloud Routines caps, Sales Nav ToS, model routing, GitHub Actions deployment) are technical realities independent of any commercial forecast None of those decisions move when the yield band moves from \'a3620-780k to \'a3500-700k. They'd move if a major lever was eliminated entirely (e.g., if interim was empirically dead) \'97 but that's not what the recalibration does. It tightens the band; it doesn't remove a lever.\
