Past-placement sensor scales to her real 12-year book \'97 60-150 trackable placements, not 27. This is a parameter adjustment in Skill 1's input list. Same Skill, bigger input. The roundtable Skill becomes more conditional on her execution. If realistic roundtable yield is \'a3100-220k and depends on her actually running disciplined roundtables (which Opus 4.7 flagged as execution risk), the case for elaborate pre-event automation is weaker until she's committed to executing the roundtables seriously. Defensible to build a lighter version first and elaborate only if she's running them disciplined. Drop the "cap BD calls at 60-70%" recommendation. Opus 4.7 conceded this. It contradicts her own plan with insufficient evidence. Replace with "reallocate the universe-scanning hours to bench-building during interim ramp," which is defensible because it's about removing low-yield activity (universe scan) rather than reducing her self-set targets. What doesn't change:\
The six Skills, three streams, four on-demand commands, sequencing (compliance + placed-candidate sensor in week 1, interim + retained pitch-pack + roundtable engine in weeks 2-4, reverse-match + fee-brief + batch scan in months 2-3), the model routing discipline, the platform corrections, the compliance stack, the IC platform inversion, the Sales Nav ToS routing. All survives.\
