Our own direct logged-off scraping \'97 Claude Code + Playwright fetching LinkedIn URLs without credentials. Technically works but LinkedIn rate-limits a single IP aggressively; after 10\'9620 requests in a day you hit login walls. Unreliable at scale. Nothing \'97 skip LinkedIn entirely, rely on Indeed/Adzuna/other sources. Bright Data gives us structured LinkedIn data at reliable scale without running our own scraping infrastructure and without credentials of any kind. That's what the \'a30 free tier / \'a3400 paid tier buys: access to their already-collected corpus.\
What Bright Data can see (honest limits) Because Bright Data only sees logged-off public pages, its dataset has everything visible to a guest visitor on LinkedIn:\
Public profile pages \'97 name, headline, current role, past roles, location, some skills Public company pages \'97 about, employee count, recent press, public posts Public job listings Public posts where the author has set them public It does not have:\
