The uncomfortable trade-off, stated plainly Your two constraints are partly in tension:\
"Leverage Recruiter comprehensively" \uc0\u8594  requires the tool to access it \u8594  requires credentials or middleware \u8594  has non-zero risk "0% risk to her account" \u8594  rules out any automation of Recruiter \u8594  tool does not leverage Recruiter You can have one or the other, not both. The honest options:\
Option A \'97 Full 0% risk (current plan). Tool never touches Recruiter. Sara uses Recruiter manually. Bright Data free tier covers the public-LinkedIn automated signal.\
Option B \'97 Middle route via Unipile (~\'8049/month). Unipile is commercial middleware that wraps LinkedIn access via her Recruiter credentials. Still technically a ToS breach but with much more sophisticated anti-detection than raw Playwright \'97 detection risk is real but lower than direct automation. This is what production recruitment-tech products use when they need Recruiter integration. Not zero risk, but meaningfully less than hand-rolled automation.\
Option C \'97 Direct credential automation. Maximum capability, maximum risk. Not recommending.\
